      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(compact): make /compact command cancelable via abortEmbeddedAgentRun",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix #66535 for OpenClaw-owned `/compact` execution: a manual context-engine compaction now becomes an abortable active embedded run while the queued compaction task is actually running, so `/stop` can find it and abort the signal passed into the compaction engine.\n\nChanges:\n- Register a synthetic active embedded-run handle inside the queued context-engine compaction task, not at command entry time.\n- Scope that synthetic active-run registration to standalone manual compaction only when no active run is already registered, so budget/preflight compaction cannot replace the real active run handle.\n- Forward caller aborts through the queued compaction signal and pass that signal to `compactContextEngineWithSafetyTimeout`.\n- Always clear the synthetic handle in `finally` after queued compaction exits.\n- Refuse to start a replacement `/compact` if an existing abortable run does not drain within 15s.\n\nCodex-native app-server compaction is intentionally not claimed as fixed here. Codex `thread/compact/start` returns immediately and real server-side cancellation requires `turn/interrupt(threadId, turnId)`, so OpenClaw should not keep a stale active-run handle for Codex-native pending compaction without a real Codex turn lifecycle owner.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:**\nBefore: `/compact` could abort an existing compaction-capable run, but the new manual context-engine compaction was not registered as an active run at the execution boundary, so `/stop` could miss it or a command-level handle could race queue ordering.\nAfter: queued context-engine compaction registers an active handle only while the queued task is executing. `/stop` aborts that handle, the engine receives an aborted `AbortSignal`, and cleanup clears the active run after completion.\n\n**Real environment tested:**\nLocal Linux checkout, Node via repo test wrapper on branch `fix/66535-compact-cancelable-refresh` at commit `39f6298bc9e17b2c3885476eb5967ec99dca40c7`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.hooks.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/runs.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.queued.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.hooks.test.ts\nnode_modules/.bin/oxlint src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.runtime.ts\nnode_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.queued.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.hooks.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.runtime.ts src/agents/embedded-agent.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.ts\ngit diff --check\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs ...\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  14 passed (14)\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  95 passed (95)\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 34.95s\n```\n\nNew/updated focused assertions include:\n- `registers queued context-engine compaction as an abortable active run`\n- `forwards the caller abort signal into the engine compact() call`\n- `does not replace an active run when abort drain times out`\n- `does not replace an existing active run handle during budget compaction`\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.queued.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.hooks.test.ts\n[qa-channel boundary dts] fresh; skipping\n[discord boundary dts] fresh; skipping\n[slack boundary dts] fresh; skipping\n[whatsapp boundary dts] fresh; skipping\n```\n\n```text\nnode_modules/.bin/oxlint src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.runtime.ts\n# passed with no findings\n```\n\n```text\nnode_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check ...\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n```\n\n```text\ngit diff --check\n# passed\n```\n\n```text\nautoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\noverall: patch is correct (0.78)\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:**\n- Queued manual context-engine `/compact` exposes an active embedded-run handle only during the queued work and only when no real active run is already registered.\n- `abortEmbeddedAgentRun(sessionId)` aborts the compaction signal while compaction is in flight.\n- The synthetic active handle is cleared after compaction exits; budget/preflight compaction preserves any existing real active run handle.\n- `/compact` no longer replaces a still-draining abortable run after a drain timeout.\n\n**What was not tested:**\n- Live gateway with a real LLM-backed `/compact` followed by `/stop`.\n- Codex app-server native compaction cancellation via `turn/interrupt(threadId, turnId)`; this PR avoids claiming that behavior.\n\nFixes: #66535\n",
